NUMBER 378
NAME Palace, entrance
MONSTER_GROUP 15
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This grand, entrance hall is filled with activity almost every hour of the
day. Various court functionaries scurry about on errands. The palace is as
awe inspiring inside as it is outside. Large scale paintings of the Royal
Family and sculptures adorn the highly polished blue stone walls. The floor
has been inlaid with a tile mosaic of the Royal Family Crest. A clerk sits
behind a polished maple desk. His job is to greet visitors and take their
names and business.
*DESCRIPTION_END
