A great set of golden double doors, inlaid with beautiful faceted rubies and the Royal Crest block the entrance to the throne room. Arrayed against the walls are various couches and chairs used by those who await an audience with the king. A herald sits behind an impressive, hexagonal desk, charged with the task of announcing visitors to the king.
