NUMBER 385
NAME Palace, throne room
MONSTER_GROUP 15
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A red silk rug leads to the Royal Throne at the northern end of this room.
The carpet is arrayed with smooth blue stone pillars at even intervals on
each side. A solid gold throne sits on top of a dais. Soft purple velvet
pillows are spread out at its feet. A stylized shield hangs above the
throne suspended on two chains with the Royal Crest engraved upon its face.
The dais also accommodates a smaller throne for the Queen Mother.
*DESCRIPTION_END
